Explanation:
- The file App\Http\Controllers\Admin\UserController.php defines a Laravel controller with methods index, edit, and update, but it does not contain any explicit route definitions (no literal path strings) nor any literals that define API paths.
- In Laravel, the routing (mapping of HTTP methods and paths to controller actions) is typically defined in routes files (e.g., routes/web.php or routes/api.php) using Route::resource or Route::get/post/etc. This file alone does not specify those paths.
- Therefore, there are no API entries to extract from this source file according to the given criteria. If you want to generate OpenAPI entries, you would need to provide the routes definitions or specify the conventional resource path (e.g., /admin/users, /admin/users/{user}, etc.) from routing configuration.
